Here we have synchronised the getInstance() method i.e. only one thread can execute this method at a
time rest will have to wait in this way only one instance is created but this has a major problem .
Suppose in getInstance() method along with the creation of object some heavy processing is also involved
which is to processed by each thread so making getInstance() method synchronised restricts other threads
from executing other tasks in this method and this makes the code inefficeint .
To resolve this issue we use Double Checked Locking Pattern or Singleton Thread Safe Block .


